      "message": "Okay. I\u0027d rather we avoid more conditional compilation. I think `MCTP_CONTROL_HANDLER` is helpful in the sense that you can patch out the entire bit of functionality, reducing binary size, but that\u0027s not what we\u0027re after here. I think we may be able to do:\n\n```\n@@ -461,7 +461,7 @@ static bool mctp_ctrl_handle_msg(struct mctp_bus *bus, mctp_eid_t src,\n                                                 buffer, length);\n                        return true;\n                }\n-       } else {\n+       } else if (MCTP_CONTROL_HANDLER_ENABLED) {\n #if MCTP_CONTROL_HANDLER\n                /* libmctp will handle control requests */\n                return mctp_control_handler(bus, src, tag_owner, msg_tag,\n```",
